	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=17327&mid=109131162210963>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=17327&mid=109131162210963>RE: lol get a clue</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=17327&mid=109131162210963#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Jul 31st 6:07 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=206863><span id=Scholar>spack</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>18 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.95]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1>lmao u guys suck... the point u never realised is wizzys have unique pants as elementals. concussion as a clicky, that means clicking while spell refreshes, so its in beetween spells perfect, and concussion... what else do you want.. all other silks get pos spell utilitys. we get dps power. so ornate sucks.. so what work ur way to elementals they will be worth it <hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE><br>I find your post completely irrelevant.&nbsp;&nbsp;Not only is it full of poor grammar and terrible spelling, but it's pointless.  You are talking of Maelin's Leggings of Lore, the elemental wizard leggings;   this is for Arantir's Leggings of Discovery, the ornate wizard leggings.  I would agree that folks should work their way to the elementals.  But, elemental leggings only drop off the elemental gods and in Plane of Time.  That is a long time and a lot of work in raiding guilds to get there.  Some are fortunate and can advance quickly.  Even when you do so, how many of your fellow raiders/guildmates are going to be competing with you for such a rare drop.  So, that settled, why don't we drop the drivel and talk about the ornate wizard legs.<br><br>Decession can be a nice thing.  Yes, the uses are limited.  The main use I've seen is typically working with a magician on a Call of the Hero chain.  The wizard Decesses the group leader to zone in (usually the safe point), group leader invites others, and then mage then CoH's.  This does not work in some zones, but it does in many.  It does in Plane of Water for example.  Wizards have the main job of DPS, but they are also very much counted on for getting people moved via TLs and such.  Accept it, it's your job.<br><br>One day I may get lucky and get an ornate leg pattern as a drop, or I may save up and buy one.  Unfortunately, the price of these on my server is high due to the fact that the enchanters get Tranquility click-cast off these.  I would say that enchanters got the best deal as far as the ornate caster pants go.  To be honest, selling these for 120k to 150k would be tempting if I did get the drop, for I do not have an enchanter.  On my server, you can get two ornate silk bracers for the price this sells for.  As a wizard, I'd rather have the mana regen four that would be gained from that, than wear these.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Aug  1 07:48:57 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
